{"title": "We need to prevent a global AI arms race now", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2023-12-08", "content": "In July, United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres suggested the establishment of an international artificial intelligence (AI) agency to govern the use of the technology.\nThis is similar to the establishment of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) in 1957 over concerns about nuclear weapons, and the suggestion prompted many to consider the parallels between the ongoing \u201cAI arms race\u201d and the nuclear arms race during the Cold War."}